task.summary: More gems added/fixed - thin loads server now
Home page and static pages created - still need content and polish
Static pages created. All info collected from existing steer clear website
jquery for address field implemented for user story #3 and user story #5. use this to figure out other jquery implementations
users can fully log in, edit, and log out for user story #3, user story #4, and user story #5
admin can now create/modify/delete users for user story #9

user views refactored to reflect DRY principles for user story #5. workers generated with devise compatibility. worker views created. worker controller created, as well as registration override. routes configured for workers. AA workers can be created/edited. Only issue that remains is that workers cannot log in (unauthorized). all for user story #7 and user story #10

workers can now log in. session controllers overridden to prevent someone from being signed in as a user and a worker simultaneously. layouts redone to properly center many views. all for user story #7, user story #9 and user story #10
alerts format properly now for bug #12. static pages modified some

shift model and controller generated. workers model modified to accomodate the concept of shifts. shifts can be created, but there is still a lot of work to be done on the worker show page (wrt js and jqurery stuff) in order to be ready to move on. this is for user story #14
fixied jquery double execution bug and issue with footer links on nested urls
more work towards starting shifts for user story #14
many partials made for user story #14. worker creation fixed for bug #19. fixed last of issues for user sign up form w.r.t address fields
workers can properly start shifts, end shifts, and indicate that they are accepting rides for user story #14.
errors made better for user story #14. also deprecated methods in forms were replaced with new methods
